This is the JSR (Jump to Subroutine) instruction.
 It saves the PC to R7 and jumps to the offset or location specified, depending
 on bit[11].
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

BR does not provide a way back, and has an option to not branch, so to speak.
 The JSR is unconditional and always jumps, but in contrast to BR provides
 a way back.
 BR can be used for programming language's conditional expressions (such
 as if's).
 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

JSR can be used to provide functions that return (such as functions in C).
